{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-11",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_11_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "The Fat Man",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 6,
  "page_start_sec": 242.21,
  "page_end_sec": 483.96,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.574,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 242.21,
      "end": 246.5,
      "text": "he shook his head grinning at her i was she insisted"
    },
    {
      "start": 247.56,
      "end": 250.14,
      "text": "no he said but if that's your story",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 250.22,
      "end": 251.16,
      "text": "it's all right with me"
    },
    {
      "start": 251.74,
      "end": 256.19,
      "text": "go see sid it's up on the next corner the pinkish building room 827",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 257.49,
      "end": 260.2,
      "text": "her blue eyes tried to probe his yellow gray ones",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 261.1,
      "end": 263.14,
      "text": "what makes you think i wasn't home she asked",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 263.26,
      "end": 266.52,
      "text": "slowly nothing except that i know you weren't"
    },
    {
      "start": 267.36,
      "end": 271.58,
      "text": "but i was i was her lips twisted and anger darkened",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 271.68,
      "end": 272.04,
      "text": "her eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 272.4,
      "end": 274.16,
      "text": "Effie Perrine told you that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 274.34,
      "end": 275.64,
      "text": "she said indignantly."
    },
    {
      "start": 275.91,
      "end": 277.9,
      "text": "I saw her looking at my clothes and"
    },
    {
      "start": 278.02,
      "end": 278.58,
      "text": "snooping around."
    },
    {
      "start": 279.39,
      "end": 280.86,
      "text": "You know she doesn't like me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 280.92,
      "end": 281.12,
      "text": "Sam."
    },
    {
      "start": 281.76,
      "end": 283.58,
      "text": "Why do you believe things she tells you when"
    },
    {
      "start": 283.58,
      "end": 286.18,
      "text": "you know she'd do anything to make trouble for me?"
    },
    {
      "start": 286.7,
      "end": 287.62,
      "text": "Jesus,"
    },
    {
      "start": 287.68,
      "end": 288.38,
      "text": "you women,"
    },
    {
      "start": 289.12,
      "end": 289.98,
      "text": "Spade said mildly.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 290.52,
      "end": 291.46,
      "text": "He looked at"
    },
    {
      "start": 291.46,
      "end": 292.44,
      "text": "the watch on his wrist."
    },
    {
      "start": 293.18,
      "end": 293.9,
      "text": "You'll have to trot along,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 294.12,
      "end": 294.38,
      "text": "precious."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.62,
      "end": 296.12,
      "text": "I'm late for an appointment now."
    },
    {
      "start": 297.02,
      "end": 297.24,
      "text": "You do",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 297.42,
      "end": 297.9,
      "text": "what you want,"
    },
    {
      "start": 298.08,
      "end": 299.14,
      "text": "but if I were you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 299.24,
      "end": 301.16,
      "text": "I'd tell Sid the truth or nothing."
    },
    {
      "start": 301.76,
      "end": 302.04,
      "text": "I mean,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 302.1,
      "end": 302.98,
      "text": "leave out the parts"
    },
    {
      "start": 302.98,
      "end": 304.12,
      "text": "you don't want to tell him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 304.74,
      "end": 306.68,
      "text": "but don't make up anything to take its place.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 307.32,
      "end": 308.74,
      "text": "I'm not lying to you,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 308.82,
      "end": 309.02,
      "text": "Sam,"
    },
    {
      "start": 309.3,
      "end": 310.07,
      "text": "she protested."
    },
    {
      "start": 310.51,
      "end": 311.7,
      "text": "Like hell you're not,"
    },
    {
      "start": 311.86,
      "end": 313.02,
      "text": "he said and stood up."
    },
    {
      "start": 313.9,
      "end": 315.58,
      "text": "She strained on tiptoe to hold her",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 315.68,
      "end": 316.36,
      "text": "face nearer his."
    },
    {
      "start": 317.32,
      "end": 318.24,
      "text": "You don't believe me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 318.4,
      "end": 319.46,
      "text": "she whispered."
    },
    {
      "start": 320.12,
      "end": 321.02,
      "text": "I don't believe you.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 322.14,
      "end": 322.62,
      "text": "And you won't",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 322.72,
      "end": 324.74,
      "text": "forgive me for for what I did?"
    },
    {
      "start": 325.29,
      "end": 326.26,
      "text": "Sure I do."
    },
    {
      "start": 326.5,
      "end": 328.18,
      "text": "He bent his head and kissed her mouth."
    },
    {
      "start": 328.832,
      "end": 329.32,
      "text": "That's all right.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 329.42,
      "end": 330.16,
      "text": "Now run along."
    },
    {
      "start": 330.78,
      "end": 332.68,
      "text": "She put her arms around him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 333.504,
      "end": 335.0,
      "text": "Won't you go with me to see Mr.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 335.14,
      "end": 335.34,
      "text": "Wise?"
    },
    {
      "start": 336.3,
      "end": 337.54,
      "text": "I can't and I'd",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 337.6,
      "end": 338.38,
      "text": "only be in the way."
    },
    {
      "start": 338.74,
      "end": 340.2,
      "text": "He patted her arms,"
    },
    {
      "start": 340.4,
      "end": 343.56,
      "text": "took them from around his body and kissed her left wrist"
    },
    {
      "start": 343.68,
      "end": 344.54,
      "text": "between glove and sleeve."
    },
    {
      "start": 345.04,
      "end": 346.78,
      "text": "He put his hands on her shoulders,"
    },
    {
      "start": 346.96,
      "end": 348.34,
      "text": "turned her to face the door and"
    },
    {
      "start": 348.64,
      "end": 349.9,
      "text": "released her with a little push."
    },
    {
      "start": 350.624,
      "end": 350.98,
      "text": "Beat it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 351.36,
      "end": 351.78,
      "text": "he ordered."
    },
    {
      "start": 353.06,
      "end": 355.32,
      "text": "The mahogany door of suite 12C at the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 355.38,
      "end": 357.94,
      "text": "Alexandria Hotel was opened by the boy"
    },
    {
      "start": 357.94,
      "end": 360.02,
      "text": "Spade had talked to in the Belvedere lobby."
    },
    {
      "start": 361.184,
      "end": 361.54,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 361.98,
      "end": 362.1,
      "text": "hello,"
    },
    {
      "start": 362.36,
      "end": 363.64,
      "text": "good-naturedly."
    },
    {
      "start": 364.02,
      "end": 365.62,
      "text": "The boy did not say anything."
    },
    {
      "start": 365.92,
      "end": 368.16,
      "text": "He stood aside holding the door open."
    },
    {
      "start": 369.184,
      "end": 369.9,
      "text": "Spade went in.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 370.66,
      "end": 372.06,
      "text": "A fat man came to meet him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 372.36,
      "end": 376.4,
      "text": "The fat man was flabbily fat with bulbous pink cheeks and"
    },
    {
      "start": 376.56,
      "end": 377.96,
      "text": "lips and chins and neck,"
    },
    {
      "start": 378.56,
      "end": 381.6,
      "text": "with a great soft egg of a belly that was all his torso,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 382.58,
      "end": 383.34,
      "text": "and pendant cones",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 383.46,
      "end": 384.52,
      "text": "for arms and legs."
    },
    {
      "start": 385.4,
      "end": 386.84,
      "text": "As he advanced to meet Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 386.94,
      "end": 389.48,
      "text": "all his bulbs rose and shook and fell separately"
    },
    {
      "start": 389.6,
      "end": 390.26,
      "text": "with each step,"
    },
    {
      "start": 390.98,
      "end": 392.48,
      "text": "in the manner of clustered soap bubbles",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 392.48,
      "end": 394.38,
      "text": "not yet released from the pipe through"
    },
    {
      "start": 394.52,
      "end": 395.34,
      "text": "which they had been blown."
    },
    {
      "start": 396.3,
      "end": 396.72,
      "text": "His eyes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 396.8,
      "end": 398.74,
      "text": "made small by fat puffs around them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 399.04,
      "end": 399.82,
      "text": "were dark and sleek."
    },
    {
      "start": 400.22,
      "end": 403.28,
      "text": "Dark ringlets thinly covered his broad scalp."
    },
    {
      "start": 403.76,
      "end": 405.36,
      "text": "He wore a black cutaway coat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 405.56,
      "end": 406.36,
      "text": "black vest,"
    },
    {
      "start": 406.6,
      "end": 409.4,
      "text": "black satin ascot tie holding a pinkish pearl,"
    },
    {
      "start": 410.112,
      "end": 412.72,
      "text": "striped gray worsted trousers and patent leather shoes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 413.92,
      "end": 415.46,
      "text": "His voice was a throaty purr.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 416.06,
      "end": 416.2,
      "text": "Ah,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 416.4,
      "end": 416.7,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 416.88,
      "end": 417.22,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 417.54,
      "end": 421.14,
      "text": "he said with enthusiasm and held out a hand like a fat pink star."
    },
    {
      "start": 422.24,
      "end": 424.18,
      "text": "Spade took the hand and smiled and said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 424.54,
      "end": 425.24,
      "text": "How do you do,"
    },
    {
      "start": 425.34,
      "end": 425.56,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 425.68,
      "end": 425.92,
      "text": "Gutman?"
    },
    {
      "start": 427.072,
      "end": 427.94,
      "text": "Holding Spade's hand,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 428.04,
      "end": 429.5,
      "text": "the fat man turned beside him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 429.6,
      "end": 432.08,
      "text": "put his other hand to Spade's elbow and guided"
    },
    {
      "start": 432.08,
      "end": 435.08,
      "text": "him across a green rug to a green plush chair"
    },
    {
      "start": 435.26,
      "end": 437.52,
      "text": "beside a table that held a siphon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 437.56,
      "end": 438.6,
      "text": "some glasses,"
    },
    {
      "start": 438.84,
      "end": 441.52,
      "text": "and a bottle of Johnny Walker whiskey on a tray,"
    },
    {
      "start": 442.0,
      "end": 443.34,
      "text": "a box of cigars,"
    },
    {
      "start": 443.46,
      "end": 444.72,
      "text": "Coronas Del Ritz,"
    },
    {
      "start": 444.88,
      "end": 445.82,
      "text": "two newspapers,"
    },
    {
      "start": 446.2,
      "end": 449.1,
      "text": "and a small and plain yellow soapstone box."
    },
    {
      "start": 450.176,
      "end": 451.84,
      "text": "Spade sat in the green chair.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 452.29,
      "end": 455.64,
      "text": "The fat man began to fill two glasses from bottle and siphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 456.14,
      "end": 456.98,
      "text": "The boy had disappeared."
    },
    {
      "start": 458.112,
      "end": 460.14,
      "text": "Doors set in three of the room's walls were shut.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 460.8,
      "end": 462.92,
      "text": "The fourth wall behind Spade was pierced by",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 462.92,
      "end": 464.86,
      "text": "two windows looking out over Gary Street."
    },
    {
      "start": 466.02,
      "end": 466.58,
      "text": "We begin well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 466.7,
      "end": 466.94,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 467.44,
      "end": 468.4,
      "text": "the fat man purred,"
    },
    {
      "start": 469.312,
      "end": 471.12,
      "text": "turning with a proffered glass in his hand.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 471.98,
      "end": 473.54,
      "text": "I just trust a man that says when.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 474.56,
      "end": 476.54,
      "text": "If he's got to be careful not to drink too much,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 476.92,
      "end": 478.96,
      "text": "it's because he's not to be trusted when he does."
    },
    {
      "start": 479.69,
      "end": 482.44,
      "text": "Spade took the glass and smiling made the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 482.54,
      "end": 483.96,
      "text": "beginning of a bow over it."
    }
  ]
}